    <table class="subsection" border="1" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
      <tr><td align="justify">
      <b>Mouse Modes:</b> Slicer has three main mouse modes that apply to the 3D viewer:  <b>Pick</b> (which allows &quot;pickable&quot; objects to be selected), <b>Place</b> (which permits objects to be interactively placed and positioned), and <b>Transform</b> (rotate, pan and zoom). The toolbar icons that switch between these mouse modes are shown from left to right above, respectively.
      </td></tr>
    </table>

    <p align="justify">
      <b>Hint:</b> These modes are persistent when selected; when you are done &quot;picking&quot; or &quot;placing&quot;, make sure to select the <b>Transform</b> mode again.
    </p>


